  article#umd
    h2 Forest loss since 2000
      span (Hansen, UMD, Google, USGS, NASA 2013)
    p This dataset uses satellite imagery to measure the area of tree cover loss annually since the year 2000, as well as measuring total tree cover in the year 2000, and average annual tree cover gain since 2000.   
    p.credits "Hansen, M. C., P. V. Potapov, R. Moore, M. Hancher, S. A. Turubanova, A. Tyukavina, D. Thau, S. V. Stehman, S. J. Goetz, T. R. Loveland, A. Kommareddy, A. Egorov, L. Chini, C. O. Justice, and J. R. G. Townshend. 2013. “High-Resolution Global Maps of 21st-Century Forest Cover Change.” Science 342 (15 November): 850–53. Data available online from: http://earthenginepartners.appspot.com/science-2013-global-forest.
    p.credits Hansen, M. C., P. V. Potapov, R. Moore, M. Hancher, S. A. Turubanova, A. Tyukavina, D. Thau, S. V. Stehman, S. J. Goetz, T. R. Loveland, A. Kommareddy, A. Egorov, L. Chini, C. O. Justice, and J. R. G. Townshend. 2013. “Hansen/UMD/Google/USGS/NASA Tree Cover Loss and Gain Area.” University of Maryland, Google, USGS, and NASA."

  article#forma
    h2 Deforestation alerts (Forma)
      span (WRI, CGD)
    p This dataset provides alerts twice every month of areas where tree cover loss is likely to have occurred. These alerts are generated through analysis of satellite images for the world’s humid tropical forests.
    p.credits Hammer, Dan, Robin Kraft, and David Wheeler. 2013. “FORMA Alerts.” World Resources Institute and Center for Global Development.

